import process
import pickle
import os
import preprocess
from plotly.subplots import make_subplots
import plotly.graph_objects as go
import plotly.io as pio
pio.renderers.default = 'notebook'
import plotly.offline as pyo
pyo.init_notebook_mode(connected=True)
import pandas as pd
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

SCORER = 'explained_variance'
COMPANY = 'NVDA'
STRATEGY = 'target_return_1d_all_returns'
TARGET = 'target_return_1d'
FEATURES = ['return_1d', 'return_2d', 'return_3d', 'return_4d',
            'return_5d', 'return_10d', 'return_21d', 'return_42d', 'return_63d']

test_len = 260 # 10 days to predict
   
# Lets try to predict stock price with pure time saries data
#read stock 
input_file = f'{COMPANY}//data//{COMPANY}_data.csv'
df = preprocess.read_data(input_file, display=True)

#time_lags = range(1,6)
#df = preprocess.add_time_lag_features(df, True)

X, y = preprocess.preprocess_data(df, TARGET, FEATURES, True)

train_end_idx = -test_len
test_start_idx = -test_len
#least_train_len = 365 # train on at least year of observations

X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test = preprocess.split_data(X, y,train_end_idx, test_start_idx, False)
print(f"Y TEST: {y_test.shape}")
sc = StandardScaler()
X_train_sc = sc.fit_transform(X_train)
X_test_sc = sc.transform(X_test)

def read_models(test_len):
    best_models=[]
    path = f"{COMPANY}//models//{STRATEGY}//{test_len}"
    for file in os.listdir(path):
        model_path = f"{path}//{file}"
        with open(model_path, "rb") as file:
            model = pickle.load(file)
        filename = os.path.basename(model_path).split('_')[0]
        best_models.append((filename, model))
    return best_models
  
best_models = read_models(test_len)
print(f"BEST MODELS: {best_models}")

def test(models, df, x_train_sc, x_test_sc, y_test, TARGET):
    df_reg_results = pd.DataFrame()
    for name, model in models:
        print(f'MODEL: {name}')
        y_pred = model.best_estimator_.predict(x_test_sc)
        print(f"Y PRED: {y_pred.shape}")
        reg_result_series = process.regression_results(y_test, y_pred, name, test_len, STRATEGY)
        df_reg_results = pd.concat([df_reg_results, reg_result_series.to_frame().T], ignore_index=True)
        reg_res_output_path = f"{COMPANY}//results//{COMPANY}_reg_test_results.csv"
        plot(train_end_idx, test_start_idx, y_pred, name)
    df_reg_results.to_csv(reg_res_output_path, mode='a', header=not os.path.exists(reg_res_output_path))
        
def plot(train_end_idx, test_start_idx, y_pred, name):
    true_values = df
    valid = df.iloc[test_start_idx:]
    valid['predictions'] = y_pred
    plt.figure(figsize=(16,8))
    plt.title(f'{COMPANY} next day prediction with {name} - all time frame')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Next day price')
    plt.plot(true_values['target_close'], color='LightSkyBlue', linewidth=2.5, label='True')
    plt.plot(valid['predictions'], color='MediumPurple', linewidth=2.5, label='Predictions')
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()  
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(16,8))
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Next day price')
    plt.title(f'{COMPANY} next day prediction with {name} - test timeframe')
    plt.plot(y_test, label = 'Test', color='LightSkyBlue', linewidth=2.5)
    plt.plot(valid['predictions'], label = 'Predictions', color='MediumPurple', linewidth=2.5)
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()  


test(best_models, df, X_train_sc, X_test_sc, y_test, TARGET)
